 of whom engages with the “idea of Africa” in their own personal way.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aBlacksxRace identityzBrazilzBahia (State). 0aBlackszBrazilzBahia (State)xEthnic identity. 0aBlackszBrazilzBahia (State)xSocial conditions. 0aGlobalizationxSocial aspectszBrazilzBahia (State). 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Pilot 2014-2015z978311060681240uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144261993740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442619937423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442619937.jpg  a978-3-11-060681-2  University of Toronto Press Pilot 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK